    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our lineup leans into favorable matchups against middle-of-the-road arms, anchored by **Corbin Carroll** (74.01) and **Josh Naylor** (71.58). **Corbin Carroll** remains our premier start; despite facing Sproat, his elite sprint speed and prime #3 spot in the order make him an essential asset in our quest for scarce stolen bases. **Josh Naylor** similarly profiles well against Bradley, T, benefitting from a +11% SP skill adjustment and a productive #4 lineup slot. While we are emphasizing offensive efficiency, the matchup for **Kyle Karros** (63.06) against Williamson is a highlight; the +19% SP skill boost and favorable wind conditions elevate him into a must-start tier, proving that targeting soft pitching is essential to our daily roster construction.\n\nStrategic depth remains a focus as we navigate the \"marginal\" start territory. **Brice Turang** (64.04) provides the best secondary value, as his position at the top of the lineup mitigates the risk posed by Rodriguez, Ed. The decision to bench **Travis Bazzana** (46.08) was the most difficult call of the morning; while he offers solid versatility, he was edged out by the superior floor provided by **Trevor Story** and **Dalton Rushing**. **Jose Caballero** remains a high-risk play today at a 41.62 score, largely suppressed by a brutal matchup against Eovaldi. With **Giancarlo Stanton** still sidelined on the IL and **Seiya Suzuki** out of the lineup entirely, we are monitoring the health of our bench closely to ensure we preserve our game caps for higher-leverage matchups later in the week.",
